<paragraph id="8BD93693F216FF96F9B2F93B471C7BE1" blockId="3.[174,1233,1759,1856]" lastBlockId="4.[166,1225,822,1841]" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="493" pageId="3" pageNumber="492">
Diagnosis. Moderately large fly with yellow body and its vestiture, and wing with yellow base, two hyaline incisions in the costal cell, two triangular hyaline incisions at anterior margin distal to vein R 
<subScript id="17E234D6F216FF91FB75F8D641097F71" attach="left" box="[548,556,1842,1856]" fontSize="6" pageId="3" pageNumber="492">1</subScript>
reaching R 
<subScript id="17E234D6F216FF91FBE2F8D641EB7F71" attach="left" box="[691,718,1842,1856]" fontSize="6" pageId="3" pageNumber="492">2+3</subScript>
and R 
<subScript id="17E234D6F216FF91FA4DF8D640137F71" attach="left" box="[796,822,1842,1856]" fontSize="6" pageId="3" pageNumber="492">4+5</subScript>
vein, correspondingly, and 3 large hyaline incision at posterior margin, separated by yellow bands: two from cell cua1 (basal reaching CuA 
<subScript id="17E234D6F211FF96F81AFC8D42767B46" attach="left" box="[331,339,873,887]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="493">1</subScript>
vein and distal entering through cell dm into r 
<subScript id="17E234D6F211FF96FAD5FC8D40BB7B46" attach="left" box="[900,926,873,887]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="493">4+5</subScript>
) and the apical crescentlike area covering almost all cell m and widely entering into cell r 
<subScript id="17E234D6F211FF96FAE3FC6D40E97BA6" attach="left" box="[946,972,905,919]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="493">4+5</subScript>
anterior of crossvein dm-cu and along costa; wing apex hyaline, at most costal vein narrowly yellow. It is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C664D10F211FF96F994FC53420D7BE1" authorityName="V. Korneyev" authorityYear="2015" box="[197,296,950,976]" class="Insecta" family="Ctenostylidae" genus="Ramuliseta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="493" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dolini">
<emphasis id="B912EA81F211FF96F994FC53420D7BE1" box="[197,296,950,976]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="493">R. dolini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, in most features, differing by the wing pattern as noted in the key.
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF19661BF211FF96F9F7FD0A47717B35" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6452673" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6452673" box="[166,1108,749,772]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6452673/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="493" startId="4.[166,199,750,772]" targetBox="[272,1051,199,697]" targetPageId="4">
<paragraph id="8BD93693F211FF96F9F7FD0A47717B35" blockId="4.[166,1108,749,772]" box="[166,1108,749,772]" pageId="4" pageNumber="493">
Fig. 3. 
<taxonomicName id="4C664D10F211FF96F9B7FD0A42D87B32" authorityName="Hennig" authorityYear="1960" box="[230,509,750,771]" class="Insecta" family="Ctenostylidae" genus="Ramuliseta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="493" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="madagascariensis">
<emphasis id="B912EA81F211FF96F9B7FD0A42D87B32" box="[230,509,750,771]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="493">Ramuliseta madagascariensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, paralectotype ♀: 
<emphasis id="B912EA81F211FF96FBF8FD0A41917B32" box="[681,692,750,771]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="493">1</emphasis>
— head dorsal, 
<emphasis id="B912EA81F211FF96FA1EFD0A407F7B32" box="[847,858,750,771]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="493">2</emphasis>
— same, right; 
<emphasis id="B912EA81F211FF96FAA0FD0A40D97B32" box="[1009,1020,750,771]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="493">3</emphasis>
— wing.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BD93693F211FF96F98AFC32421C7C21" blockId="4.[166,1225,822,1841]" pageId="4" pageNumber="493">
Description. Head as described for 
<taxonomicName id="4C664D10F211FF96FBF1FC3340217BC1" authority="Korneyev, 2015" authorityName="V. Korneyev" authorityYear="2015" box="[672,772,982,1008]" class="Insecta" family="Ctenostylidae" genus="Ramuliseta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="493" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dolini" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="B912EA81F211FF96FBF1FC3340217BC1" box="[672,772,982,1008]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="493">R. dolini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22157FAF211FF96FA5DFC3340687BC0" box="[780,845,983,1009]" pageId="4" pageNumber="493" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, in 
<typeStatus id="54DD8831F211FF96FA2BFC32473D7BC1" box="[890,1048,982,1008]" pageId="4" pageNumber="493">paralectotype</typeStatus>
conspicuously compressed.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD93693F211FF96F98AFBF242917C81" blockId="4.[166,1225,822,1841]" pageId="4" pageNumber="493">
Thorax as described for 
<taxonomicName id="4C664D10F211FF96F8A1FBF341777C01" authority="Korneyev, 2015" authorityName="V. Korneyev" authorityYear="2015" box="[496,594,1046,1072]" class="Insecta" family="Ctenostylidae" genus="Ramuliseta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="493" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dolini" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="B912EA81F211FF96F8A1FBF341777C01" box="[496,594,1046,1072]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="493">R. dolini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22157FAF211FF96FB06FBF341B17C00" box="[599,660,1047,1073]" pageId="4" pageNumber="493" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
Scutum bearing: 0 acrostichal, 2–3 dorsocentral, 2 posterior notopleural, 1 intraalar and 1 postalar seta. Postpronotal lobe without setae, but 1–3 setae and 4–6 smaller setulae. Scutellum with 2 pairs of setae (basal and apical) and 15–20 irregular setulae on disk and margin. Prosternum transverse, sclerotised at posteroventral margin.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD93693F211FF96F98AFB5340E77CE0" blockId="4.[166,1225,822,1841]" box="[219,962,1206,1233]" pageId="4" pageNumber="493">
Legs yellow, with yellow setulae, as described for 
<taxonomicName id="4C664D10F211FF96FA4BFB5340587CE1" authority="Korneyev, 2015" authorityName="V. Korneyev" authorityYear="2015" box="[794,893,1206,1232]" class="Insecta" family="Ctenostylidae" genus="Ramuliseta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="493" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dolini" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="B912EA81F211FF96FA4BFB5340587CE1" box="[794,893,1206,1232]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="493">R. dolini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22157FAF211FF96FAD5FB5340E77CE0" box="[900,962,1207,1233]" pageId="4" pageNumber="493" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD93693F211FF96F98AFB3247B17D80" blockId="4.[166,1225,822,1841]" pageId="4" pageNumber="493">
Wing as on 
<figureCitation id="135D2A16F211FF96F822FB3242EB7CC1" box="[371,462,1238,1264]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[166,199,750,772]" captionTargetBox="[272,1051,199,697]" captionTargetId="figure-449@4.[228,1133,172,735]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 3. Ramuliseta madagascariensis, paralectotype ♀: 1 — head dorsal, 2 — same, right; 3 — wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6452673" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6452673/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="493">
fig. 3, 
<emphasis id="B912EA81F211FF96F891FB3242EB7CC1" box="[448,462,1238,1264]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="493">3</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
. Vein M almost parallel to R 
<subScript id="17E234D6F211FF96FA67FB0D40757CC6" attach="left" box="[822,848,1257,1271]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="493">4+5</subScript>
; ratio of its three last sections: M2: M3: M4 = 1: 0.9: 1.2. Wing pattern, as in most ctenostylines, with yellow basal cells and well-developed pattern of connected yellow crossbands and rounded subapical yellowbrown area separated by yellow bands: two from cell cua 
<subScript id="17E234D6F211FF96FA1CFAAD40707D66" attach="left" box="[845,853,1353,1367]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="493">1</subScript>
(basal reaching CuA 
<subScript id="17E234D6F211FF96FD00FAAD477C7D66" attach="left" box="[1105,1113,1353,1367]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="493">1</subScript>
vein and distal entering through cell dm into r 
<subScript id="17E234D6F211FF96FB0FFA8D415C7D46" attach="left" box="[606,633,1385,1399]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="493">4+5</subScript>
) and the apical crescent-like area covering almost all cell m and widely entering into cell r 
<subScript id="17E234D6F211FF96FBDAFA6D41807DA6" attach="left" box="[651,677,1417,1431]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="493">4+5</subScript>
anterior of crossvein dm-cu and along costa; wing apex is hyaline, at most costal vein narrowly yellow. The rest as in 
<taxonomicName id="4C664D10F211FF96FABDFA7347757D81" authority="Korneyev, 2015" authorityName="V. Korneyev" authorityYear="2015" box="[1004,1104,1430,1456]" class="Insecta" family="Ctenostylidae" genus="Ramuliseta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="493" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dolini" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="B912EA81F211FF96FABDFA7347757D81" box="[1004,1104,1430,1456]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="493">R. dolini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22157FAF211FF96FD07FA7347B17D80" box="[1110,1172,1431,1457]" pageId="4" pageNumber="493" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD93693F211FF96F98AFA5242907EA1" blockId="4.[166,1225,822,1841]" pageId="4" pageNumber="493">Abdomen yellow. Syntergite 1+2 yellow, 1.7 times as long as wide, slightly longer than tergites 3–6 combined; tergites 5 and 6 with large laterobasal black spots. Sternites yellow, black setulose. Sternite 1 longitudinal trapezoid, as well as sternite 2, with clear seam between them; sternites 3–6 subquadrate, poorly sclerotized. Membrane without any setulae, short microtrichose. Oviscape convex, yellow, yellow setulose, as long as tergites 3–6 combined. Oviscape simple, tubular, with microtrichose cercal unit, flexibly joined to its apico-dorsal surface</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD93693F211FF96F98AF97340317E80" blockId="4.[166,1225,822,1841]" box="[219,788,1686,1713]" pageId="4" pageNumber="493">
Measurements. Body 
<quantity id="4C9E9B76F211FF96F88BF97241107E80" box="[474,565,1686,1713]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.4" pageId="4" pageNumber="493" unit="mm" value="8.4">8.4 mm</quantity>
, wing 
<quantity id="4C9E9B76F211FF96FBD0F97240357E80" box="[641,784,1686,1713]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.3" metricValueMax="7.4" metricValueMin="7.2" pageId="4" pageNumber="493" unit="mm" value="7.3" valueMax="7.4" valueMin="7.2">7.2–7.4 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD93693F211FF96F98AF95242B07EE1" blockId="4.[166,1225,822,1841]" box="[219,405,1718,1744]" pageId="4" pageNumber="493">Male unknown.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD93693F211FF97F98AF93347037978" blockId="4.[166,1225,822,1841]" lastBlockId="5.[174,1233,175,330]" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="494" pageId="4" pageNumber="493">
D i s c u s s i o n. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF74B62F211FF96F8D2F93241417EC0" author="Hennig, W." box="[387,612,1750,1777]" pageId="4" pageNumber="493" pagination="321 - 353" refId="ref5006" refString="Hennig, W. 1960. Pyrgotidae de Madagascar (Diptera). Memoires de l'Institut Scientifique de Madagascar. Ser. E, 11 (1959), 321 - 353." type="journal article" year="1960">Hennig (1960: 327)</bibRefCitation>
described this species based on 
<specimenCount id="9D60FD1AF211FF96FA87F93347477EC1" box="[982,1122,1750,1777]" pageId="4" pageNumber="493" type="female">two females</specimenCount>
, without designation of 
<typeStatus id="54DD8831F211FF96F80AF91242E07F21" box="[347,453,1782,1808]" pageId="4" pageNumber="493">holotype</typeStatus>
, so both specimens were 
<typeStatus id="54DD8831F211FF96FBADF91340417F20" box="[764,868,1783,1809]" pageId="4" pageNumber="493">syntypes</typeStatus>
; the subsequent statement by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF74B62F211FF96F9F7F8F241067F00" author="Pereira-Colavite, A. &amp; Mello, R. L." box="[166,547,1814,1841]" pageId="4" pageNumber="493" pagination="215 - 223" refId="ref5382" refString="Pereira-Colavite, A., Mello, R. L. 2014. Catalogue of the Ctenostylidae (Diptera, Schizophora) of the World. Zootaxa, 3838 (2), 215 - 223." type="journal article" year="2014">Pereira-Colavite &amp; Mello (2014)</bibRefCitation>
that one of them is a 
<typeStatus id="54DD8831F211FF96FA76F8F240AB7F01" box="[807,910,1814,1840]" pageId="4" pageNumber="493">holotype</typeStatus>
and the other one is paratype, based on the labels they bear, is therefore erroneous. I herewith designate the specimen deposited in MHNP (good condition, both wings and most legs present) as 
<typeStatus id="54DD8831F210FF97FD37FF2B47F578D8" box="[1126,1232,207,233]" pageId="5" pageNumber="494">lectotype</typeStatus>
and the specimen deposited in SDEI (fair condition: head shriveled, all tarsi and tibiae and femora of 3 legs missing, left wing partly broken; one wing and abdomen detached and possibly are stored separately on slides, but not located by far) as 
<typeStatus id="54DD8831F210FF97FAD1FECB47077978" box="[896,1058,303,329]" pageId="5" pageNumber="494">paralectotype</typeStatus>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
